<br>
Anyway, I might find a place to dump the pic, but the stats are: Feet 15 ac 25 dex 15 int 25 agi 85 hp 110 mana 30 Disease Resist 30 Magic Resist.  Pretty nice stats honestly, but most people with Yelinak boots wouldn't bother taking (being we're on a hybrid DKP system).  But the kicker was this: Focus Effect: Wind of the Nightcrawler.<br>
<br>
After these dropped for the first time, we asked 'lucy' what it was, and the effect came up and listed exactly like Enhancment Haste III.  Which happens to be on Ring of the Shissar and my Yunnb's Earring.  So I'm thinking, ah, cool, at some point if I ever get rid of those, this will come in handy.<br>
<br>
The kicker came the next day.  We killed VXAHR then camped for the day.  I was really busy on Saturday and actually logged in when AHR was at about 95%, got cothed up real fast and was dropping mods when I noticed &quot;Your Slippers of Dark Whispers begins to glow.&quot;  I'm thinking, &quot;what the hell!?!&quot;  I never bothered to look to see if the rest of the spells I had were affected (I have Dain Cloak with Spell Haste 3 and Ring of Lightning with Summoning haste 3).  Low and behold (wish I could drop this picture, but I can't)  Mod Rod 2 went from 4.5 second to 3.2 seconds, Coth from 12 to 8.4 seconds.  I was really surprised at this.  It really made my day, then I noticed something else.  Normal summons were also dropped by 30% in spell casting time (now I actually don't have my epic, yes but you raid constantly for 2 years and find time to do epic when I really hate doing quests).  So epic summons is also affected by this.<br>
<br>
The other kicker to this is I don't have any Quick Summoning AAs, where most mages that far into VT generally do.  However, there is a very nice bonus to this, you only need QS 2 to max out spell haste with these boots.  It can save 9 points, which frankly, is really nice.<br>
<br>
<br>
